:Class Tester2
‚ćĚ This class provides a test framework for APL applications.
‚ćĚ ## Warning
‚ćĚ This is **not** an introduction into how the test framework works, and how you should organize your test cases.
‚ćĚ This is, after all, a technical documentation.\\
‚ćĚ More information for the _user_ of `Tester2` is available on
‚ćĚ [`Tester2`'s home page on GitHub ](https://github.com/aplteam/Tester2).\\
‚ćĚ Note that in case after running `RunGUI` the GUI stays around your have two choices of getting rid of the GUI
‚ćĚ programmatically: either call the `CloseGUI` method from your instance or erase the instance altogether.
‚ćĚ ## INI files
‚ćĚ `Tester2` tries to find two INI files: "Testcases.INI" and "Testcases_{computername}.INI". If it finds one or
‚ćĚ both of them it will merge and flatten them and assign them to the `INI` property of `Tester2` instance.
‚ćĚ ## Dependencies
‚ćĚ `Tester2` requires the classes `APLTreeUtils2` and `CodeCoverage`, but the latter only in case you want code
‚ćĚ coverage to be checked; for that you need to set the `codeCoverage` property.
‚ćĚ ## Misc
‚ćĚ Home page: <https://github.com/aplteam/Tester2>\\
‚ćĚ Author: Kai Jaeger

    ‚éēIO‚Üź1 ‚čĄ ‚éēML‚Üź1

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźVersion;ref
      :Access Public shared
    ‚ćĚ Returns the version number from `TatinVars` if possible.
    ‚ćĚ See also `History`
      :If 0<‚éēNC'TatinVars.CONFIG'
          r‚Üź(‚éēJSON‚ć†('Dialect' 'JSON5')‚äĘTatinVars.CONFIG).version
      :ElseIf 0<##.‚éēNC'TatinVars.CONFIG'
          r‚Üź(‚éēJSON‚ć†('Dialect' 'JSON5')‚äĘ##.TatinVars.CONFIG).version
      :Else
    ‚ćĚ When a script was not loaded with Tatin, there will be no namespace `TatinVars`.
    ‚ćĚ In such cases we cannot provide a version number, so we return just ''.
          :If '#.Tester2.TestCases.'{‚ćļ‚Č°(‚ČĘ‚ćļ)‚ÜĎ‚ćĶ}‚ćē‚éēTHIS
              ‚ćĚ Runs in its own testcases, and therefore won't find the correct function without help
              ref‚Üź‚äÉ‚äÉ‚éēCLASS ‚éēTHIS
              r‚Üźref.Version
          :Else
              r‚Üź''
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
