    ‚ąá r‚ÜźHistory
      :Access Public shared 
      ‚ćĚ * 4.3.0 ‚čĄ 2025-09-13
      ‚ćĚ   * Packages updated
      ‚ćĚ * 4.2.0 ‚čĄ 2025-06-05
      ‚ćĚ   * `Cleanup` (as well as group-specific `Cleanup` functions) may now return a (optional) boolean indicating success (1) or failure (0).\\
      ‚ćĚ      (Up to version 4.2 a result, if any, was ignored.
      ‚ćĚ   * The reports on `Cleanup` and `Cleanup_<group>` is now more precise
      ‚ćĚ   * `Cleanup` and `Cleanup_<group>` are now executed under :Trap. Problems are reported in the log rather than crashing the test suite.  
      ‚ćĚ   * Bug fixes
      ‚ćĚ     * The message concerning the "Cleanup" function repeated "found and executed" twice
      ‚ćĚ * 4.1.0 ‚čĄ 2025-05-30
      ‚ćĚ   * `EstablishHelpers` now prints a `]Link.Add` statement to the session when appropriate
      ‚ćĚ   * `EstablishHelpers` does not do anything anymore in case the helpers are already established
      ‚ćĚ   * `GetTestTemplate` now prints a `]Link.Add` statement to the session when appropriate
      ‚ćĚ   * Dependencies updated (FilesAndDirs)
      ‚ćĚ   * Bug fixes
      ‚ćĚ     * `Prepare` did not work without `Tester2` being opened as a Cider project
      ‚ćĚ     * `Prepare` does not ask for code coverage reports when the CodeCoverage class is not around
      ‚ćĚ     * The documentation did not embedd the CSS
      ‚ćĚ     * Some minor issues fixed in the documentation
      ‚ćĚ     * Assigning a custom return code could crash `Tester2.ReportTestResults`
      ‚ćĚ * 4.0.0 ‚čĄ 2025-04-03
      ‚ćĚ   * Potenially breaking change: `Version` now returns the package config version number as a char vector
      ‚ćĚ   * Packages updated
      ‚ćĚ   * `Make` improved
      ‚ćĚ * 3.11.1 ‚čĄ 2024-12-30
      ‚ćĚ   Bug fixes
      ‚ćĚ   * In `Version`: if for some reason it cannot find `TatinVars` it should return
      ‚ćĚ     an empty vector for the version number rather than crashing.
      ‚ćĚ   * Reports were intended to honour ‚éēPW but got one char too long
      ‚ćĚ * 3.11.0 ‚čĄ 2024-12-25
      ‚ćĚ   * `ListTestFunctions` enhanced
      ‚ćĚ   * `Version` extracts the version number now from the package config file
      ‚ćĚ * 3.10.0 ‚čĄ 2024-11-30
      ‚ćĚ   * Dependencies updated in order to make Tester2 ready for 20.0 (IniFiles)
      ‚ćĚ * 3.9.1 ‚čĄ 2024-10-03
      ‚ćĚ   * Comment added according to issue #25
      ‚ćĚ   * Bug fix: the new '?'-syntax did not work when 3 (for "Cleanup") was selected
      ‚ćĚ * 3.9.0 ‚čĄ 2024-10-01
      ‚ćĚ   * The term `stopFlag` was used in two different ways: on the level of the test framework and inside
      ‚ćĚ     test functions. This required a change: inside test functions, what was initially called
      ‚ćĚ     `stopFlag` is now called `debugFlag`.\\
      ‚ćĚ     Note that the old name is still supported in order to support old test cases, so this is not a
      ‚ćĚ     breaking change.
      ‚ćĚ   * `stopFlag` is not necessarily a Boolean anymore, making the name a misnomer.
      ‚ćĚ     Therefore, it was renamed to `stop`.
      ‚ćĚ   * All `Run*`-functions that accept `stop` as a left argument now allow it to be "?".
      ‚ćĚ     This led to a list with all options the user may select from.
      ‚ćĚ * 3.8.0 ‚čĄ 2024-08-03
      ‚ćĚ   * `RunThese` accepts now a list of names identifying test functions (like `Foo_001` or `Test_Foo_001)
      ‚ćĚ * 3.7.0 ‚čĄ 2024-03-02
      ‚ćĚ   * The restriction that "," and "*" cannot go together has been lifted.
      ‚ćĚ   * The restriction that `~` could only be used at the beginning has been lifted
      ‚ćĚ   * Bug fixes
      ‚ćĚ     *
      ‚ćĚ * 3.6.0 ‚čĄ 2024-01-11
      ‚ćĚ   * Any a general `Initial` function as well as any group-specific one can now return a text vector
      ‚ćĚ     rather than a Boolean. Empty=success, otherwise it is treated as an error msg and reported.
      ‚ćĚ   * So far, in case a test suite was executed in batch mode, there was no information provided which
      ‚ćĚ     line did cause a test case to fail.
      ‚ćĚ   * Shared method `Help` added that provides a full documentation of Tester2.
      ‚ćĚ * 3.5.0 ‚čĄ 2023-04-28
      ‚ćĚ   * Helpers updated
      ‚ćĚ\\
      ‚ćĚ For a full history (including older versions) see <https://github.com/aplteam/Tester2/releases>
