    ‚ąá {(rc log)}‚Üź{stop}Run debugFlag
    ‚ćĚ Runs _all_ test cases, by default with error trapping.\\
    ‚ćĚ The Boolean right argument decides whether with (0) or without (1) error trapping.\\
    ‚ćĚ In addition you may specify an optional left argument which will make `Run` stop in certain circumstances:
    ‚ćĚ * 1 = stop just before any test case is about to be executed
    ‚ćĚ * 2 = stop in all `Initial*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * 4 = stop in all `Cleanup*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * ? = gives you a list to select from\\
    ‚ćĚ You may also specify a sum of them, like 3, 5, 6 or 7
    ‚ćĚ DO NOT localyze `_parms` in this function!
      :Access Public Instance
      stop‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0}'stop'
      ‚Üí(‚ć¨‚Č°stop‚ÜźProcessStop stop)/0
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert(‚äāstop)‚ąä0 1 2 4 3 5 6 7
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert 1=‚Č°,stop
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert 1=‚ČĘstop
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert 83=‚éēDR stop
      'Invalid right argument 'Assert(‚äādebugFlag)‚ąä0 1
      _parms‚ÜźCreateParms ‚ć¨
      _parms.debugFlag‚ÜźdebugFlag
      _parms.stop‚Üźstop
      _parms.trapFlag‚Üź~debugFlag
      (rc log)‚ÜźRun__ _parms
     ‚ćĚDone
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {(rc log)}‚Üź{parms}RunGUI these
    ‚ćĚ Runs `these` test cases, which defaults to _all_ in case `these` is empty.\\
    ‚ćĚ The user can set all sorts of parameters via the GUI.\\
    ‚ćĚ Note that this is a Windows-only feature.\\
    ‚ćĚ The left argument is useful only for defining defaults on the GUI.\\
    ‚ćĚ See also `Run` which does vasically the same but without a GUI.\\
    ‚ćĚ DO NOT localyze `_parms` in this function!
      :Access Public Instance
      :If 'Win'‚Č°A.GetOperatingSystem''
          _parms‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ CreateParms ‚ć¨}'parms'
          CloseGUI
          _parms.testCaseNos‚Üźthese
          _parms.guiFlag‚Üź1
          _parms.testCaseNos‚Üźthese
          (rc log)‚ÜźRun__ _parms
      :Else
          'RunGUI is Windows-only'‚éēSIGNAL 11
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {(rc log)}‚Üź{stop}RunThese these;rc;ref2Gui
    ‚ćĚ Run just the specified tests.
    ‚ćĚ `these` can be one of:
    ‚ćĚ * A scalar or vector of numbers identifying ungrouped test cases.
    ‚ćĚ * A text string that uniquily identifies a group.
    ‚ćĚ * A text string that ends with an asterisk (`*`) identifying one or more test groups.
    ‚ćĚ * A nested vector with names of test functions (like `Test_Foo_002` or just `Foo_002`).\\
    ‚ćĚ   This is particularly useful if you want to execute, say, just the test cases that have recently been changed.
    ‚ćĚ * A two-item vector with:
    ‚ćĚ   * A text string identifying one or more groups (with the wildcard syntax, **not** by specifying more than one).
    ‚ćĚ   * An integer vector identifying test cases within that group.\\
    ‚ćĚ Note that you cannot mix different syntaxes.\\
    ‚ćĚ You may specify an optional left argument which will make `RunThese` stop in certain circumstances:
    ‚ćĚ * 1 = stop just before any test case is about to be executed
    ‚ćĚ * 2 = stop in all `Initial*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * 4 = stop in all `Cleanup*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * ? = gives you a list to select from\\
    ‚ćĚ You may also specify a sum of them, like 3, 5, 6 or 7.\\
    ‚ćĚ The result:
    ‚ćĚ 1. A return code. 0 means all test cases passed successfully.
    ‚ćĚ 2. A vector of text vectors with the log. The log contains detailed information about what was carried out.
    ‚ćĚ DO NOT localyze `_parms` in this function!
      :Access Public Instance
      stop‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0}'stop'
      ‚Üí(‚ć¨‚Č°stop‚ÜźProcessStop stop)/0
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert(‚äāstop)‚ąä0 1 2 4 3 5 6 7
      _parms‚ÜźCreateParms ‚ć¨
      _parms.testCaseNos‚Üźthese
      _parms.debugFlag‚Üź1
      _parms.trapFlag‚Üź0
      _parms.stop‚Üźstop
      (rc log)‚ÜźRun__ _parms
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {(rc log)}‚Üź{stop}RunBatchTests debugFlag
    ‚ćĚ Runs all test cases but tells the test functions that this is a batch run, meaning that test cases in need
    ‚ćĚ for any human being for interaction should abort themselves and return `_NoBatchTest` instead.\\
    ‚ćĚ By default any errors are trapped.
    ‚ćĚ In addition you can specify an optional left argument which will make `RunBatchTests` stop in certain circumstances:
    ‚ćĚ * 1 = stop just before any test case is about to be executed
    ‚ćĚ * 2 = stop in all `Initial*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * 4 = stop in all `Cleanup*` functions
    ‚ćĚ * ? = gives you a list to select from\\
    ‚ćĚ You may also specify a sum of them, like 3, 5, 6 or 7.\\
    ‚ćĚ This function does not trap errors in case `debugFlag` is 1.\\
    ‚ćĚ Returns 0 for okay or a 1 as `rc` in case one or more test cases are broken or failed.\\
    ‚ćĚ DO NOT localyze `_parms` in this function!
      :Access Public Instance
      stop‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0}'stop'
      ‚Üí(‚ć¨‚Č°stop‚ÜźProcessStop stop)/0
      'Invalid left argument 'Assert(‚äāstop)‚ąä0 1 2 4 3 5 6 7
      'Invalid right argument 'Assert(‚äādebugFlag)‚ąä0 1
      _parms‚ÜźCreateParms ‚ć¨
      _parms.debugFlag‚ÜźdebugFlag
      _parms.stop‚Üźstop
      _parms.batchFlag‚Üź1
      _parms.trapFlag‚Üź~debugFlag
      _parms.testCaseNos‚Üź‚ć¨
      (rc log)‚ÜźRun__ _parms
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźHelp
      :Access Public Shared
      r‚Üź']open ',##.TatinVars.GetFullPath2AssetsFolder,'Tester2-Reference.html'
    ‚ąá

    ‚ćĚ‚ćĚ‚ćĚ Private stuff

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźCreateParms dummy
   ‚ćĚ Creates a parameter space to be consumed by `Run__` and therefore by any of the `Run*` functions
   ‚ćĚ that do call `Run__`. The namespace is populated with defaults.\\
   ‚ćĚ 1. `trapFlag`: controls error trapping:
   ‚ćĚ    * 1 = failing test cases are reported, then the next one is executed.
   ‚ćĚ    * 0 = program halts in case of an error - use this for investigation.
   ‚ćĚ 2. `debugFlag`: if it is 1 failing tests stop for investigation (stop on error).
   ‚ćĚ 3. `batchFlag`: a 1 would mean that the test should quit itself if for example it
   ‚ćĚ     needs a human being in front of the monitor. Such test cases are supposed to
   ‚ćĚ     do nothing but return `_NoBatchTest` when this flag is on.
   ‚ćĚ 4. `stop`: is treated as "stop just before the next test case is going to be executed" when 1.\\
   ‚ćĚ     Since version 2.4 this accepts also an integer that can be the sum of:
   ‚ćĚ     * 1=stop just before any test case is executed
   ‚ćĚ     * 2=stop in all `Initial*` functions
   ‚ćĚ     * 4=stop in all `Cleanup*` functions
   ‚ćĚ 5. `testCaseNos`: the test cases to be executed (IDs or group or a mixture of both)
   ‚ćĚ 6. `guiFlag`: is 0 when no GUI is required an 1 otherwise.
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź‚éēNS''
