                  ‚éē‚Üźbuff
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
     
     ‚ąÜstop_before_test:  ‚ćĚ To switch off the stopping mechanism permanently, enter:   ps.stop‚Üź0
      rc‚Üźref.‚ćéfnsName,' ',(‚ćēps.debugFlag),' ',(‚ćēps.batchFlag)
     
      :If 0<‚ČĘ_exec_after_each_test
          :If 0=1 1‚äÉ‚éēAT _exec_after_each_test
              ‚ćé_exec_after_each_test,' fnsName ps'
          :Else
              :If 0<‚ČĘbuff‚Üź‚ćé_exec_after_each_test,' fnsName ps'
                  ‚éē‚Üźbuff
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      :If 0<‚ČĘ_codeCoverage
          _codeCoverage.Stop ‚ć¨
      :EndIf
    ‚ćĚDone
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá QuitTests;was
    ‚ćĚ Use this method to quit a test run prematurely and make sure that everything is tidied up,
    ‚ćĚ meaning that a `Cleanup` function (if any) is executed.\\
      :Access Public Instance
      ‚ąÜTRAPS_IN_SESSION‚Üź600‚Ć∂0  ‚ćĚ Enable traps in the session and save original setting
      ‚éēSIGNAL QuitEvent
    ‚ąá


    ‚ąá {r}‚Üź{type}ShowLog msg;selog;buff
    ‚ćĚ `type` may be 1 or 2 or 3 or ¬Į1 or ¬Į2:
    ‚ćĚ * A 1 means an action message
    ‚ćĚ * A 2 means the result of the execution attempt of a test function.
    ‚ćĚ * A 3 means "to be appended the very last line in the log"
    ‚ćĚ * A negative type means message with more to come
    ‚ćĚ Requires semi-global `ps`: a parameter space with `ps.log` being, well, the log.
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      :If 0<‚ČĘmsg
          type‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 1}'type'
          'Invalid type'Assert(‚äā|type)‚ąä1 2 3
          :If ps.batchFlag‚ąß0=ps.guiFlag
              :If type=3
                  ps.log[‚ČĘps.log]‚Üź‚äā((‚ČĘps.log)‚äÉps.log),msg
              :Else
                  :If 1<‚Č°msg
                      ps.log,‚Üźmsg
                  :Else
                      ps.log,‚Üź‚äāmsg
                  :EndIf
              :EndIf
          :Else
              buff‚Üź{1=‚Č°‚ćĶ:‚äā‚ćĶ ‚čĄ (3‚Č†‚ČĘ‚ćĶ)‚ą®'---'‚Č°3‚ÜĎ‚äÉ‚ćĶ:‚ćĶ ‚čĄ ‚äā(1‚äÉ‚ćĶ),' ',(2‚äÉ‚ćĶ),' ',(3‚äÉ‚ćĶ)}msg
              :If ps.guiFlag
                  :If ps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.‚ąÜClosed
                      ‚éēSIGNAL QuitEvent
                  :EndIf
                  :If 3=type
                  :AndIf 1=‚Č°msg
                      ps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.Text[‚ČĘps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.Text]‚Üź‚äā(‚äÉ‚ĆĹps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.Text),msg
                  :Else
                      ps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.Text,‚Üź‚äÜmsg
                  :EndIf
                  ps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.SelText‚Üź2‚ćī(‚ČĘps.ref2Gui.‚ąÜn.Log.Text),¬®1
              :EndIf
              :If type=3
                  ps.log[‚ČĘps.log]‚Üź‚äā((‚ČĘps.log)‚äÉps.log),‚äÉbuff
              :Else
                  ps.log,‚Üźbuff
              :EndIf
              :If ~ps.guiFlag
                  :If type=3
                      ‚éē‚Üź‚äÉ¬Į1‚ÜĎps.log
                  :ElseIf ¬Į1‚Č†√ótype
                      selog‚Üź{1=‚Č°‚ćĶ:‚ćĶ ‚čĄ (3‚Č†‚ČĘ‚ćĶ)‚ą®'---'‚Č°3‚ÜĎ‚äÉ‚ćĶ:‚ć™‚ćĶ ‚čĄ (1‚äÉ‚ćĶ),' ',(2‚äÉ‚ćĶ),' ',(3‚äÉ‚ćĶ)}msg
                      :If type<0
                          ‚ćě‚Üźselog,(type=¬Į2)/CR
                      :Else
                          ‚éē‚Üźselog
                      :EndIf
                  :EndIf
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

