    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźoldName RenameTestFnsTo newName;body;rc;header;comment;res;name;right;left;delFilanme;list;this;no;buff;val;f1;f2
     ‚ćĚ Renames a test function or a group of test functions and tells acre and Link.\\
     ‚ćĚ `oldName` and `newName` **must not** contain a dot.\\
     ‚ćĚ Note that names of test functions are supposed to start with "Test_", so if the arguments do not start
     ‚ćĚ with "Test_" the string is added.
     ‚ćĚ Examples:
     ‚ćĚ ```
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_999'   ‚Üź 'Test_001' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'Test_999'     ‚ćĚ Rename a single test function without group
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_BBB_2' ‚Üź 'Test_1' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'Test_BBB_2'     ‚ćĚ Rename a single test function with group
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_BBB_2' ‚Üź 'BBB_1' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'BBB_2'           ‚ćĚ Rename a single test function with group without "Test_"
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_CCC_3' ‚Üź 'Test_BBB_2' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'Test_CCC_3' ‚ćĚ Change group and number
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_YYY*'  ‚Üź 'Test_AAA; T.RenameTestFnsTo 'Test_YYY'     ‚ćĚ Rename all members of a group with full name
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_YYY*'  ‚Üź 'AAA' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'YYY'               ‚ćĚ Rename all members of a group without "Test_"
     ‚ćĚ 'Test_VVV*'  ‚Üź '' T.RenameTestFnsTo 'Test_VVV'             ‚ćĚ all NOT belonging to a group are renamed
     ‚ćĚ ```
     ‚ćĚ `r ‚Üź ‚ć¨`
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      (oldName newName)‚ÜźoldName newName~¬®' '
      'Names must not contain dots'Assert~‚ÜĎ‚ą®/'.'‚ąä¬®oldName newName
      (oldName newName)‚Üź'Test_'‚ąė{‚ćļ‚Č°(‚ČĘ‚ćļ)‚ÜĎ‚ćĶ:‚ćĶ ‚čĄ ‚ćļ,‚ćĶ}¬®oldName newName
      :If 0=‚ČĘbuff‚ÜźListGroups
          f1‚Üź0
          f2‚Üź0=‚ČĘRemove‚ąÜTest_ oldName
      :Else
          f1‚Üź(‚äāRemove‚ąÜTest_ oldName)‚ąä(‚ČĘ'Test_')‚Üď¬®{‚ćĶ[;1]}buff     ‚ćĚ Group name?
          f2‚Üź0=‚ČĘRemove‚ąÜTest_ oldName
      :EndIf
      :If f1
          'New name is invalid'Assert ¬Į1‚Č†‚éēNC Remove‚ąÜTest_ newName
