    :Section Helpers
    ‚ąá Prepare;testPath;testFilename;ask;answer;options;flag;ind
‚ćĚ Creates an instance of the class `Tester2` named `T` and configures it for
‚ćĚ Assumes that the project is handled by the project manager "Cider", and that there is
‚ćĚ a namespace ##.CiderConfig available with the Cider config parameters.
‚ćĚ As a side effect is creates a folder "TestResults" in the project's root folder if the
‚ćĚ user wants to do code coverage with the `CodeCoverage` class.
      ‚éēIO‚Üź1 ‚čĄ ‚éēML‚Üź1
      T‚Üź‚éēNEW Tester2 ‚éēTHIS
      testPath‚Üź##.CiderConfig.HOME,'/TestResults'
      testFilename‚ÜźtestPath,'/CodeCoverage'
      flag‚Üź0
      :If 9=‚éēNC'CodeCoverage'
      :AndIf ‚éēNEXISTS testPath
          :If ‚éēNEXISTS testFilename,'.profile'
              ind‚Üź('Code Coverage' 0 1)CommTools.Select'Append' 'Replace' 'Neither'
              ‚Üí(3=ind)/0
              flag‚Üź1
              :If 2=ind
                  1 CodeCoverage.DeleteFiles testFilename
              :EndIf
          :Else
              flag‚Üź0 CommTools.YesOrNo'Code coverage?'
          :EndIf
      :Else
          flag‚Üź0 CommTools.YesOrNo'Code coverage?'
      :EndIf
      :If flag
          3 ‚éēMKDIR testPath  ‚ćĚ
          T.codeCoverage‚Üź‚éēNEW CodeCoverage(,‚äā'#.',{‚ćĶ,'.',‚ćĶ}2‚Üď‚ćē‚éēTHIS.##)
          T.codeCoverage.filename‚ÜźtestFilename
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá RunTests;htmlFilename;verbose;option
‚ćĚ 1. Prepares the test framework
‚ćĚ 2. Runs all test cases
‚ćĚ 3. Processes the code coverage data (if collected)
‚ćĚ 4. Asks the user whether the code coverage report should be put on view
      Prepare
      T.Run 1
      :If 0<‚ČĘT.codeCoverage
          {}CodeCoverage.ProcessData T.codeCoverage.filename
          option‚Üź'Type of code coverage report' 0 1 CommTools.Select'Overview' 'Verbose' 'None'
          :If 3>option
              verbose‚Üź2=option
              htmlFilename‚Üźverbose CodeCoverage.CreateReport T.codeCoverage.filename
              ‚éē‚Üź']Open file://',htmlFilename
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (success log)‚ÜźRunTestsInBatchMode;rc
‚ćĚ Runs all test with the batch flag on and the debug flag off.
‚ćĚ Returns a two-item vector:\\
‚ćĚ [1] Boolean with 1 indicating success and 0 failure\\
‚ćĚ [2] A vector of character vectors with the messages
      Prepare
      (rc log)‚ÜźT.RunBatchTests 0
      success‚Üźrc=0
    ‚ąá

    :EndSection

:EndClass
